cs.CV, cs.MED, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a 3D ultrasound-based tracking system for precise prostate biopsy sample localization. The proposed method involves image registration and optimization techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses medical imaging (cs.MED) and graphics (cs.GR) aspects related to the proposed system. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on prostate volumes, which suggests that the proposed method can be used for medical imaging applications (cs.MM).
